      "writtenOn": "2026-07-07T21:48:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Agree that the string-keyed unpackProperties isn\u0027t the ideal async idiom. It\u0027s here\nto read EID/SupportedMessageTypes from the InterfacesAdded payload we already\nhold, avoiding a per-endpoint Get/GetAll (Chinmay asked for the inline read on\nPS1). The generated client accessors all go through get_property/\nget_all_properties, so switching to them reintroduces the round-trip.\n\nThe clean fix is the sdbusplus addition you mention: the generated .properties()\nalready contains the exact PropertiesVariant-map -\u003e properties_t decode -- it\u0027s\njust chained onto get_all_properties(). I\u0027ll extract that into a standalone\ndecode_properties(a{sv}) on the client harness so the typed decode works on a\npayload we already have; this call site then becomes decode_properties(\nendpointProps) -- typed and no round-trip. I\u0027ll put that up as a separate\nsdbusplus change and switch this over once it lands, keeping\nunpackPropertiesNoThrow here in the meantime so this change isn\u0027t blocked on it. Would that be OK?",
      "parentUuid": "63006dc9_e8a8950b",
      "revId": "9d7dfe1f91e8c8f56248ada11fcf4493dc49ee55",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
